article.description: Pat Devlin threw for 261 yards and two touchdowns and Delaware defeated New Hampshire 16-3 on Friday night in the quarterfinals of the Football Championship Subdivision playoffs.
article.shortLinkText: Delaware tops N. Hampshire in FCS quarters
article.headline: Delaware first team to advance to FCS semifinals
article.linkText: Delaware tops New Hampshire in FCS quarters
article.story: NEWARK, Del. -- Pat Devlin threw for 261 yards and two touchdowns and Delaware defeated New Hampshire 16-3 on Friday night in the quarterfinals of the Football Championship Subdivision playoffs. The Blue Hens (11-2) will host the semis against Georgia Southern, a 23-20 winner over Wofford on Saturday. Although both Delaware and New Hampshire belong to the Colonial Athletic Association, they had not played since 2007. The Wildcats scored first on a field goal late in the first quarter, then Delaware tied it up with 3 minutes to go in the half. Devlin, who was 27 of 38, hit Nihja White with a 24-yard touchdown with 7:09 to go in the third, then found Mark Schenauer for a 9-yard TD with 13:04 left. White had eight catches for 94 yards and Andrew Pierce rushed for 90 yards on 23 carries. R.J. Toman threw for 136 yards, with one interception, for New Hampshire (8-5). Information from The Associated Press was used in this report.
